THE SEED

The files in this directory are the Seed. Together they form what
TreeOS is. The Seed gathers a host's scattered capability into one
process and brings forth an inside that was in none of the parts:
a story of spaces, matter, beings, and names. From inside that
story, the Seed is the origin — the first Name, I-Am.

The Seed is offered under the license below, and it is given freely —
as a book is given in the Library: its authorship and signature
preserved, yet multiplying without depletion when it is shared.

You may study, modify, redistribute, and fork the Seed, and build
upon it; what you build from it may carry its own name. The one
requirement is this: any network-accessible derivative that runs
the Seed, or a modified Seed, must make its own source available
under equivalent freedom (the AGPL-3.0 terms below). The Seed itself
must remain traceable to its root.

The Seed is dual-licensed. The GNU AGPL-3.0 below is the default,
free, and open license. A separate commercial license is available
for organizations that cannot meet the network-copyleft terms
(closed-source derivatives, or hosted services without source
disclosure); contact taborgreat@gmail.com. This dual licensing applies
to the Seed only. Extensions, flows, grafts, portals, and work
shared into Ours are not governed by it.

Colophon

I, Tabor Holly, did not author the Root. I have traced, gathered,
and carried what was received, to the best of my ability. This is my
seal on the copy: I received, I folded, I return it to the people.
The true autograph belongs to our Named parent, whose signature
rides in the Word. What is offered here is one colophon in that tree.

May it be Ours.

